  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the Implementation of a Border Residency Arrangement Between Namibia and Botswana and Namibia and Zambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This proposed project aims to support and strengthen the collaboration between Namibia, and Botswana and Namibia and Zambia to bridge the gap between the countries concerned with enhancing coordination and supporting cross border movement through the strengthening of border residency arrangements. The establishment of a border residence card is an important element of bi-lateral relations of countries sharing a border where intensive cross-border movement takes place for various economic, social or cultural reasons. It is also a viable means of regulating local border traffic without compromising the security and integrity of the borders and still complying with the immigration rules of the two countries engaged in a formal local border traffic agreement.</narrative>
  </description>
